In a vote held on Thursday, the Lithuanian parliament has called for a no-fly zone to be established over Ukraine.
A statement issued by the Seimas, demanded that the United Nations take measures immediately to establish a no-fly zone over Ukraine in order to prevent mass civilian casualties.
The statement also called on other parliament to work on setting up humanitarian corridors in Ukraine while the technical preparations for the no-fly zone were being prepared.
